A member of the House of Representatives from Rivers State, Hon. Doctor Farah Dagogo, has said the presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar would address Nigeria’s challenges if elected. He spoke yesterday during a sensitisation parley with Atiku’s supporters in Port Harcourt, the Rivers State capital. The lawmaker said, “Part of the problems that had bedeviled our country in recent times is the need to address the restructuring menace and that of resource control, which is paramount to the people of the Niger Delta and other regions in the country with natural resources.” Not a ‘clean-sweep Ignatius’ Why Nigerians must mornitor mock BVAS accreditation – INEC Chair Atiku’s five-point-agenda is tailored towards; restoring Nigeria’s unity, strengthening national security, fostering economic prosperity, improving educational delivery and restructuring. 